<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-72-0852 </DOCNO><TEXT>The IEA Coal Industry Advisory Board (CIAB) undertook, in May 1986, astudy to examine the effects of lower oil prices on major coal producersand on the potential for coal displacement in the electric utility sector.This report represents an independent analysis by the CIAB. It is basedon the analysis and experience of major coal producers in Australia,Canada and the United States and a large number of electric utilitiesin North America, Europe and Japan. The special position of electricityproducers in the United States has been treated in depth. 1 fig., 14tabs.</TEXT></DOC>